OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1776265866
OL,3,CMums of teen knife crime victims call
OL,4,Cfor change in youth anonymity law
OL,6,FThree mothers, who all lost their
OL,7,Fteenage sons to knife crime, say
OL,8,Fchanges must be made to the law to
OL,9,Fallow young people convicted of murder
OL,10,Fto be named.
OL,12,FUnder current legislation, anyone
OL,13,Funder the age of 18 involved in
OL,14,Fcriminal proceedings is granted
OL,15,Fanonymity unless a judge decides it is
OL,16,Fin the public interest to lift
OL,17,Freporting restrictions.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/14
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
