PN,43702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1776265866
OL,3,CMums of teen knife crime victims call
OL,4,Cfor change in youth anonymity law
OL,6,FIt is a part of the law that the
OL,7,Fmothers of Max Dixon and Mason Rist,
OL,8,FOwen Dunn and Mikey Roynon all want to
OL,9,Fsee changed.
OL,11,FLeanne Ekland's son Max Dixon died
OL,12,Falong with his best friend Mason Rist
OL,13,Fafter the pair were stabbed to death
OL,14,Fnear their home in Bristol in January
OL,15,F2024.
OL,17,FMax Dixon's mother Leanne tells ITV
OL,18,FNews she is living in a 'nightmare'
OL,19,Fevery day following her son's murder
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/14
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,438,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1776265866
OL,3,CMums of teen knife crime victims call
OL,4,Cfor change in youth anonymity law
OL,6,FFive people are currently serving life
OL,7,Fsentences for the murder of Max, 16,
OL,8,Fand his friend, Mason, 15, in what was
OL,9,Fa case of mistaken identity. But two
OL,10,Fof their killers have never been
OL,11,Fnamed, as they are still under 18.
OL,13,FLeanne told ITV News she feels she is
OL,14,Fstill waiting for justice after her
OL,15,Fson's death.
OL,17,F"I live in a nightmare. I relive it
OL,18,Fevery day", Leanne said. "I try not to
OL,19,Fbut I do. He was an innocent child",
OL,20,Fshe added.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/14
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,438,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1776265866
OL,3,CMums of teen knife crime victims call
OL,4,Cfor change in youth anonymity law
OL,6,F"I'm still waiting for my justice, I
OL,7,Fknow eventually when they reach 18,
OL,8,Fthey're going to be named anyway so
OL,9,FI'm waiting for that to happen.
OL,11,F"I've got another two years for one of
OL,12,Fthem to be named and that's going to
OL,13,Fbring it all back to me again two
OL,14,Fyears down the line.
OL,16,F"It's going to come flooding back to
OL,17,Fme what happened that night, if they
OL,18,Fwere named in the beginning I could
OL,19,Fprocess things and I could move past
OL,20,Fthat.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/14
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,438,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1776265866
OL,3,CMums of teen knife crime victims call
OL,4,Cfor change in youth anonymity law
OL,6,F"If they're capable of carrying these
OL,7,Fweapons, I don't say knives because
OL,8,Fthey weren't knives, they used
OL,9,Fmachetes and a sword. If they're big
OL,10,Fenough to carry those weapons around
OL,11,Fand use them, why are we protecting
OL,12,Fthem?"
OL,14,F"It doesn't matter if they were 10
OL,15,Fyears old. They should have been
OL,16,Fnamed. None of those boys gave Max and
OL,17,FMason a chance to fight back.
OL,19,F"I can never get my head around that,
OL,20,Fwhy they did that and then walk away
OL,21,Fand not get named."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/14
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
